{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/releases/4553589", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/releases/4553589/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/releases/4553589/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/snayfach/MIDAS/releases/tag/v1.2.0", "id": 4553589, "author": {"login": "snayfach", "id": 2104237, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIxMDQyMzc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2104237?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach", "html_url": "https://github.com/snayfach", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTQ1NTM1ODk=", "tag_name": "v1.2.0", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Version 1.2.0", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2016-11-02T22:28:22Z", "published_at": "2016-11-02T22:44:03Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/tarball/v1.2.0", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/zipball/v1.2.0", "body": "Fixes bugs introduced in v1.1 and switches back to v1.0 strategy for estimating gene content.\nCode and reference database should be stable going forward.\n\n1) uses new database format\n-pan-genome genes defined at 99% identity threshold (same as v1.0)\n-includes mapping of genes to gene clusters at lower % identity thresholds (75,80,85,90,95)\n-enables sensitive read mapping while giving flexibility in defining pan genome gene families\nfor other info, see: http://lighthouse.ucsf.edu/MIDAS/README.txt\n\n2) updated build_midas_db.py\n-provides same features described in (1)\n\n3) disabled map quality filtering in pan-genome pipeline (--mapq)\n-when genes are clustered at 99% identity, reads will often map to >1 gene, receive a low mapping quality, and get discarded\n-this feature was disabled to retain these reads\n\n4) bug fixes\n-fixed estimation of marker gene coverage in 'run_midas.py species' (bug introduced in v1.1)\n-fixed normalization by marker gene coverage in 'run_midas.py genes'\n\n5) 'run_midas.py genes' and 'merge_midas.py genes' report # of reads mapped to each gene cluster\n"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/releases/4480992", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/releases/4480992/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/releases/4480992/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/snayfach/MIDAS/releases/tag/v1.1.0", "id": 4480992, "author": {"login": "snayfach", "id": 2104237, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIxMDQyMzc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2104237?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach", "html_url": "https://github.com/snayfach", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/snayfach/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTQ0ODA5OTI=", "tag_name": "v1.1.0", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Version 1.1.0", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2016-10-25T18:12:55Z", "published_at": "2016-10-25T18:20:24Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/tarball/v1.1.0", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/snayfach/MIDAS/zipball/v1.1.0", "body": "1) uses new database format\n   species_ids now include the genus and species (ex: Bacteroides_vulgatus_57955)\n   pan-genome genes now defined at 95% identity threshold\n   removed 16S database for species profiling\n   for other info, see: http://lighthouse.ucsf.edu/MIDAS/README.txt\n\n2) run_midas.py and merge_midas.py require specification of database path\n   enables users to specify their own database, or different versions of default database\n\n3) improved run_midas.py snps\n  -increased speed and decreased memory usage\n  -fixed bug when computing depth at sites with N's\n  -fixed bug when reference allele is not ATCG\n\n4) added new scripts\n  -build_midas_db.py\n   allows users to build their own reference database\n  -call_consensus.py\n   calls consensus alleles at core-genomic sites\n   enables construction of inter-sample phylogenetic trees\n  -compare_genes.py\n   quantify inter-sample differences in gene content\n  -snp_diversity.py\n   quantify intra and inter-sample population diversity\n\n5) updated documentation\n"}
